22#ifndef search_list_h
23#define search_list_h
24
25/* Non-Posix systems use semi-colon as directory separator in lists,
26 since colon is part of drive letter spec. */
27#if defined (__MSDOS__) || defined (_WIN32)
28#define PATH_SEP_CHAR ';'
29#else
30#define PATH_SEP_CHAR ':'
31#endif
32
33typedef struct search_list_elem
34 {
35 struct search_list_elem *next;
36 char path[1];
37 }
38Search_List_Elem;
39
40typedef struct
41 {
42 struct search_list_elem *head;
43 struct search_list_elem *tail;
44 }
45Search_List;
46
47extern void search_list_append (Search_List *, const char *);
48
49#endif /* search_list_h */
